FilterData API 

High-performance API for normalization and quality scoring of contact data (PII) before importing into CRM and marketing systems.

FilterData converts unstructured contact dumps from Excel, forms and CRM exports into clean, normalized and quality-scored records.

Typical use cases:

CRM data imports

marketing mailing lists

lead databases

contact deduplication pipelines

Core Features
Phone normalization (RU)

Input numbers are converted to international format.

Example:

8 (999) 123-45-67

Result:

+79991234567

The system removes:

spaces

brackets

dashes

non-digit symbols

and converts Russian numbers starting with 8 → +7.

Email normalization

The system performs:

trimming

lowercase conversion

syntax validation

Example:

User@GMAIL.com

Result:

user@gmail.com
Email typo detection (Levenshtein)

The engine detects possible typos in common email domains using Levenshtein distance.

Checked domains:

gmail.com
yahoo.com
outlook.com
hotmail.com
icloud.com
mail.ru
yandex.ru

Example:

Input

user@agmil.com

Output

email: user@agmil.com
qc: 2
warnings: ["email_domain_typo"]

The system does not auto-correct the domain.
It only flags the record as RISK.

Name normalization

Names are cleaned and normalized:

иВан12

Result

Иван

Processing includes:

removing digits

fixing capitalization

removing invalid symbols

limiting name length to three words

Mixed alphabet detection

The engine detects mixed Cyrillic / Latin characters.

Example:

Ивaн

(Latin "a")

Such records are marked as:

QC = RISK

This prevents CRM search issues and duplicate records.

Data Quality Scoring

Each processed record receives a quality score (QC).

QC	Status	Description
0	VALID	Data is clean and fully usable
1	ACCEPTABLE	Minor issues (for example only first name)
2	RISK	Possible typo or mixed alphabet
3	PARTIAL	Incomplete or suspicious data
4	MISSING	Field is empty or unusable

Example response:

{
  "phone": "+79991234567",
  "name": "Иван Иванов",
  "email": "example@mail.com",
  "qc": 0,
  "qc_breakdown": {
    "phone": 0,
    "name": 0,
    "email": 0
  },
  "warnings": []
}
Batch Processing

The API supports batch processing.

Up to 1000 contacts per request.

This significantly reduces request overhead when processing large datasets.

Performance

Typical performance metrics:

Latency: ~12-15 ms per request
Core normalization engine: ~700-800 RPS
Batch endpoint: ~400-500 RPS

Performance depends on hardware and configuration.

